To increase Likes, Comments, and Shares on an existing post on your Facebook Business Page, the best option is to use Boost Post or create an Engagement Campaign in Meta Ads Manager.

//Option 1: Boost Post (Easy)///////////////

Go to your Facebook Page.
- Find the post you want to promote.
- Click Boost Post.
- Choose goal: Get More Engagement / More Post Engagement.

Set audience:
- Location (country/city)
- Age
- Gender
- Interests

Set budget:
- Daily budget or total budget.
- Example: $5/day for 5 days.
- Select duration.

Add payment method.
Click Boost Now.

This will help increase:
✔ Likes
✔ Comments
✔ Shares
✔ Reactions

//Option 2: Meta Ads Manager (Best Control)///////////////////

Use Meta Ads Manager for better targeting.

Step 1: Create Campaign
  Objective: Engagement
Step 2: Choose Conversion Location
  Select On your ad.
Step 3: Choose Engagement Type
  Select Post Engagement
Step 4: Select Existing Post
  Choose your existing Page post.
Step 5: Audience Targeting

Example:

Country: United States
Age: 18–45
Interests related to your business
Step 6: Placements

Use:

Facebook Feed
Instagram Feed
Stories
Reels

Step 7: Budget

Start with:
$2–$10/day
Tips to get more comments/shares

Use CTA in caption:

“What do you think? Comment below!”
“Tag your friend”
“Share if you agree”

Ask questions in post:
Example:
👉 “Which design do you like most?”



Best strategy
-----------------------------
First 1–2 days:
Run Post Engagement campaign.

Then:
Create Page Likes or Traffic campaign for scaling.

